Roughy_3 <- Roughy_1 %>% 
  mutate(GbyS= paste(Ground,sex,sep = "_")) %>%  #new variable to combine Ground and sex

  mutate(sumsum = cumsum(Length))


#create function to find the mode
Mode <- function(x) {
    if (is.numeric(x)) {
        x_table <- table(x)
        return(as.numeric(names(x_table)[which.max(x_table)]))
        }
}

#calcuate the mode
Roughy_mode <- Roughy_3 %>% 
  dplyr::group_by(year,GbyS) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(Mode = Mode(x = Length))%>%
  spread(GbyS, Mode) 
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
#calcuate the  counts
Roughy_nos <- Roughy_3 %>% 
  dplyr::group_by(year, GbyS) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(Numbers = n())%>%
  spread(GbyS, Numbers)

note that this graph has been corrected. The 2019 report the combined Lyle formula was incorrect. The Lyle formula for Males (Lyle_com_Males) was used instead of the combined sex formula (Lyle_com)
``` r Lyle_com <- function(x) {(0.037 * (x) ^ 2.952)} #Lyle_com_Males <- function(x) {(0.037 * (x) ^ 2.942)} S2019_fun <- function(x) {(0.056 * (x) ^ 2.8502)} S2019M_fun <-function(x) {(0.073 * (x) ^ 2.7685)} S2019F_fun <-function(x) {(0.071 * (x) ^ 2.7945)}
RoughyWeight<- Roughy%>% filter(year==2019) %>% drop_na(weight_kg) %>% filter(weight_kg != 0) %>% mutate(weight_g = weight_kg *1000) %>% mutate(year=as.factor(year))

annotate(‘text’, x = 22, y = 3800, size =4,hjust =0, label = expression(paste(“Weight”[“Lyle sex combined”]^{}, ” = 0.037 * Length”^{2.952})))+
